ontrols.Control.Background%2A&gt;</ph> to \"Red\" or \"MediumBlue\".","pos":[1684,1798],"source":"  For example, you can set a button's <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Control.Background%2A> to \"Red\" or \"MediumBlue\"."},{"content":"For a list of other predefined solid color brushes, see the static properties of the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Brushes&gt;</ph> class.","pos":[1800,1927],"source":"  For a list of other predefined solid color brushes, see the static properties of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Brushes> class."},{"content":"The following is an example.","pos":[1928,1956]},{"content":"Choose a color from the 32-bit color palette by specifying the amounts of red, green, and blue to combine into a single solid color.","pos":[2189,2321]},{"content":"The format for specifying a color from the 32-bit palette is \"<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>#rrggbb<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>\", where <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>rr<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept> is a two digit hexadecimal number specifying the relative amount of red, <bpt id=\"p3\">*</bpt>gg<ept id=\"p3\">*</ept> specifies the amount of green, and <bpt id=\"p4\">*</bpt>bb<ept id=\"p4\">*</ept> specifies the amount of blue.","pos":[2323,2555],"source":"  The format for specifying a color from the 32-bit palette is \"*#rrggbb*\", where *rr* is a two digit hexadecimal number specifying the relative amount of red, *gg* specifies the amount of green, and *bb* specifies the amount of blue."},{"content":"Additionally, the color can be specified as \"#<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>aarrggbb<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>\" where <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>aa<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept> specifies the <bpt id=\"p3\">*</bpt>alpha<ept id=\"p3\">*</ept> value, or transparency, of the color.","pos":[2557,2685],"source":"  Additionally, the color can be specified as \"#*aarrggbb*\" where *aa* specifies the *alpha* value, or transparency, of the color."},{"content":"This approach enables you to create colors that are partially transparent.","pos":[2686,2760]},{"content":"In the following example, the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Control.Background%2A&gt;</ph> of a <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Button&gt;</ph> is set to fully-opaque red using hexadecimal notation.","pos":[2762,2942],"source":"  In the following example, the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Control.Background%2A> of a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Button> is set to fully-opaque red using hexadecimal notation."},{"content":"Use property tag syntax to describe a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush&gt;</ph>.","pos":[3161,3243],"source":"Use property tag syntax to describe a <xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush>."},{"content":"This syntax is more verbose but enables you to specify additional settings, such as the brush's opacity.","pos":[3244,3348]},{"content":"In the following example, the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Control.Background%2A&gt;</ph> properties of two <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Button&gt;</ph> elements are set to fully-opaque red.","pos":[3349,3525],"source":" In the following example, the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Control.Background%2A> properties of two <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Button> elements are set to fully-opaque red."},{"content":"The first brush's color is described using a predefined color name.","pos":[3526,3593]},{"content":"The second brush's color is described using hexadecimal notation.","pos":[3594,3659]},{"pos":[3930,3969],"content":"Painting with a SolidColorBrush in Code","linkify":"Painting with a SolidColorBrush in Code","nodes":[{"content":"Painting with a SolidColorBrush in Code","pos":[0,39]}]},{"content":"To paint an area with a solid color in code, use one of the following options.","pos":[3973,4051]},{"content":"Use one of the predefined brushes provided by the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Brushes&gt;</ph> class.","pos":[4061,4153],"source":"Use one of the predefined brushes provided by the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Brushes> class."},{"content":"In the following example, the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Control.Background%2A&gt;</ph> of a <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Button&gt;</ph> is set to <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Brushes.Red%2A&gt;</ph>.","pos":[4154,4333],"source":" In the following example, the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Control.Background%2A> of a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Button> is set to <xref:System.Windows.Media.Brushes.Red%2A>."},{"content":"Create a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush&gt;</ph> and set its <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush.Color%2A&gt;</ph> property using a <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Color&gt;</ph> structure.","pos":[4585,4764],"source":"Create a <xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush> and set its <xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush.Color%2A> property using a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Color> structure."},{"content":"You can use a predefined color from the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Colors&gt;</ph> class or you can create a <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Color&gt;</ph> using the static <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Color.FromArgb%2A&gt;</ph> method.","pos":[4765,4970],"source":" You can use a predefined color from the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Colors> class or you can create a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Color> using the static <xref:System.Windows.Media.Color.FromArgb%2A> method."},{"content":"The following example shows how to set the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush.Color%2A&gt;</ph> property of a <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush&gt;</ph> using a predefined color.","pos":[4981,5160],"source":"The following example shows how to set the <xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush.Color%2A> property of a <xref:System.Windows.Media.SolidColorBrush> using a predefined color."},{"con