RadialGradientBrush&gt;</ph>.","pos":[6687,6909],"source":"[!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winclient](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-winclient-md.md)] provides two types of gradient brushes: <xref:System.Windows.Media.LinearGradientBrush> and <xref:System.Windows.Media.RadialGradientBrush>."},{"pos":[6956,6972],"content":"Linear Gradients","linkify":"Linear Gradients","nodes":[{"content":"Linear Gradients","pos":[0,16]}]},{"content":"A <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.LinearGradientBrush&gt;</ph> paints an area with a gradient defined along a line, the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>gradient axis<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.","pos":[6976,7099],"source":"A <xref:System.Windows.Media.LinearGradientBrush> paints an area with a gradient defined along a line, the *gradient axis*."},{"content":"You specify the gradient's colors and their location along the gradient axis using <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientStop&gt;</ph> objects.","pos":[7101,7233],"source":"  You specify the gradient's colors and their location along the gradient axis using <xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientStop> objects."},{"content":"You may also modify the gradient axis, which enables you to create horizontal and vertical gradients and to reverse the gradient direction.","pos":[7235,7374]},{"content":"The gradient axis is described in the next section.","pos":[7375,7426]},{"content":"By default, a diagonal gradient is created.","pos":[7427,7470]},{"content":"The following example shows the code that creates a linear gradient with four colors.","pos":[7477,7562]},{"content":"This code produces the following gradient:","pos":[7988,8030]},{"pos":[8037,8210],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">![</bpt>A diagonal linear gradient<ept id=\"p1\">]</ept><bpt id=\"p2\">(../../../../docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/media/wcpsdk-graphicsmm-diaglgradient-nolabel.jpg \"</bpt>wcpsdk_graphicsmm_diaglgradient_nolabel<ept id=\"p2\">\")</ept>","source":"![A diagonal linear gradient](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/media/wcpsdk-graphicsmm-diaglgradient-nolabel.jpg \"wcpsdk_graphicsmm_diaglgradient_nolabel\")"},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> The gradient examples in this topic use the default coordinate system for setting start points and end points.","pos":[8217,8337],"source":"**Note:** The gradient examples in this topic use the default coordinate system for setting start points and end points."},{"content":"The default coordinate system is relative to a bounding box: 0 indicates 0 percent of the bounding box and 1 indicates 100 percent of the bounding box.","pos":[8338,8489]},{"content":"You can change this coordinate system by setting the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientBrush.MappingMode%2A&gt;</ph> property to the value <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.BrushMappingMode&gt;</ph>.","pos":[8490,8667],"source":" You can change this coordinate system by setting the <xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientBrush.MappingMode%2A> property to the value <xref:System.Windows.Media.BrushMappingMode>."},{"content":"An absolute coordinate system is not relative to a bounding box.","pos":[8668,8732]},{"content":"Values are interpreted directly in local space.","pos":[8733,8780]},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientStop&gt;</ph> is the basic building block of a gradient brush.","pos":[8787,8880],"source":"The <xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientStop> is the basic building block of a gradient brush."},{"content":"A gradient stop specifies a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientStop.Color%2A&gt;</ph> at an <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientStop.Offset%2A&gt;</ph> along the gradient axis.","pos":[8882,9041],"source":"  A gradient stop specifies a <xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientStop.Color%2A> at an <xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientStop.Offset%2A> along the gradient axis."},{"content":"The gradient stop's <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientStop.Color%2A&gt;</ph> property specifies the color of the gradient stop.","pos":[9051,9171],"source":"The gradient stop's <xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientStop.Color%2A> property specifies the color of the gradient stop."},{"content":"You may set the color by using a predefined color (provided by the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Colors&gt;</ph> class) or by specifying ScRGB or ARGB values.","pos":[9172,9319],"source":" You may set the color by using a predefined color (provided by the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Colors> class) or by specifying ScRGB or ARGB values."},{"content":"In <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)]</ph>, you may also use hexadecimal notation to describe a color.","pos":[9320,9454],"source":" In [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](../../../../includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)], you may also use hexadecimal notation to describe a color."},{"content":"For more information, see the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Color&gt;</ph> structure.","pos":[9455,9529],"source":" For more information, see the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Color> structure."},{"content":"The gradient stop's <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientStop.Offset%2A&gt;</ph> property specifies the position of the gradient stop's color on the gradient axis.","pos":[9539,9692],"source":"The gradient stop's <xref:System.Windows.Media.GradientStop.Offset%2A> property specifies the position of the gradient stop's color on the gradient axis."},{"content":"The offset is a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Double&gt;</ph> that ranges from 0 to 1.","pos":[9693,9754],"source":" The offset is a <xref:System.Double> that ranges from 0 to 1."},{"content":"The closer a gradient stop's offset value is to 0, the closer the color is to the start of the gradient.","pos":[9755,9859]},{"content":"The closer the gradient's offset value is to 1, the closer the color is to the end of the gradient.","pos":[9860,9959]}